value.0: This boredom will dull our senses.
Is there something else you need from me, <FirstName>?
<StartAction>[Her eyes follow you, calculating. She merely nods and watches you go.]</Start>
Are you certain you have need of me? You seem to have plenty of assistance.
My skills and expertise will be better spent here than in a large party. Unless the situation changes, I will be here.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> No, I'm sorry. It's just not my style. I will be waiting for you here unless the party situation changes.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Alright, you've convinced me. In return, I'll be taking a cut of the gold and treasure we find.
I was hoping you would ask. I would gladly journey with you. Far better to be active than to sit around waiting. I'll be taking a cut of the spoils we find, of course.
So now you know everything... the Valsharess, who we are, why we're here, all of it. What we're doing here is very important.
Oh, really? It doesn't concern you that she is a danger to your world as well as mine?
You want to wait for the Valsharess on the surface, for when she's at her strongest? Even if that wasn't the case, doesn't the fact that she wishes you dead worry you in the slightest?
It doesn't rest solely on you. Our lives are on the line here, as well. The Seer and her people abandoned their homes on the surface to fight the Valsharess, should you do any less?
And even if that means nothing to you, what about the fact that the Valsharess wishes you dead? Does that not worry you in the slightest?
How about yourself, then? Does the fact that the Valsharess wants you dead not worry you in the slightest?
I see. Even were that the case, does the fact that the Valsharess wants you dead not worry you in the slightest?
My understanding is that the Valsharess has already attacked your surface world. Even if she could not do so again, doesn't the fact she wants you dead worry you?
Now I'm not sure if you're being serious or not. The Valsharess is no joke.
Bravado. Does the fact that the Valsharess wishes you dead not worry you in the slightest?
You've seen the proof, have you not? Your surface world attacked... and were you not attacked by the Valsharess's forces? Are none of these things proof of our words?
Good. And even was that not enough, wouldn't the fact that the Valsharess wishes you dead worry you in the slightest?
Then do not trust us. It makes no difference, so long as you act. If nothing else, the Valsharess wishes you dead... does that not worry you at all?
You think it will be fun, do you? Doesn't the fact that the Valsharess wants you dead worry you in the slightest?
Short of defeating her. Perhaps the Seer was correct, after all. I suppose we shall see.
Well, you have confidence, I'll grant you that. Let's hope it serves you well.
Truly? Then perhaps the Seer was correct, after all. I suppose we shall see.
It looks to me like you have enough assistance at the moment. I must protect the Seer... that is my first responsibility. If you truly have need of me later, however, I will gladly go with you.
My skills and expertise will be better spent here than in a large party. Unless the situation changes, I will be here.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> No. Journeying with you will be irresponsible given the situation. I will assist you when it looks like you need the help.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Perhaps you do require my assistance. Far better to be active than to wait here for the Valsharess to act. I will be taking my cut of the spoils, however.
I was hoping you would ask. I would gladly journey with you. Far better to be active than to wait here for the Valsharess to act. I will be taking my cut of the spoils, however.
Yes? Is there something you need?
Part ways? Are you... are you certain? I like to think my skills are quite useful, especially in our current situation.
You won't regret this, <FirstName>.
As you wish, though I think you are making a mistake. I will go back to the temple in Lith My'athar. If you change your mind, you can come find me there.
I'm sorry, but I'm working with someone else now.
You're going to want to speak to the Seer. Trust me, she can explain everything.
Only a fool dares to cross me!
I should go.
I could use an assassin. Would you be willing to join me?
Fine. Forget I asked.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Be that as it may, I'll need all the help I can get, my friend.
I couldn't care less about the Valsharess.
Of course it concerns me. That's why I should be up there and not down here.
Perhaps. I don't see why the burden should rest solely on me, however.
No. Why would I worry about what happens to others?
I really doubt it's as world-shattering a danger as you all make it out to be.
There is no way she is a danger to the surface world.
I agree. A drow queen teamed up with a powerful devil? Deadly combination.
They will be once I'm through with them.
I have yet to receive proof that any of this is true.
I suppose maybe they are.
I have no reason to trust anything you say or do.
Proof of the Valsharess, yes. I have no proof of your motivations.
I am absolutely serious. They must be stopped, without question.
And it sounds like it will be quite the adventure! I can't wait!
Of course it does. There is nothing I can do about that, however.
If I worried always about the possibility of dying, I would never accomplish anything.
She should be more worried about me. And it seems she is.
I'm doing what I must, for the good of all.
I could use an assassin. Would you be willing to join me?
Fine. Forget I asked.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Be that as it may, I'll need all the help I can get to put a stop to the Valsharess.
Never mind.
I think we need to part ways.
All right, fine. Stay with me, then.
Go on. Maybe we'll meet later.
I'd like to buy off some of the loot that you picked up.
